---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import HorizontalCard from "../components/HorizontalCard.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title = "We need you!" sideBarActiveItemID="join us">
  
    <div class="flex text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5 justify-left">We need you!</div>
    <div class="flex text-lg w-full  mb-4 justify-left">Join us and help us run this thing. You can sign up to volunteer for :</div>

<article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
<ol class="list-decimal">
    <ul>    -  <b>Investigative Journalism:</b> You will be talking to a lot of people, gathering information, experiences, and accounts (in any language), and then articulate and consolidate them into articles.</ul>

    <ul>    -  <b>Reporting/Interviewing:</b> You will be reporting on the events occurring on campus, such as club events, protests, etc.</ul>

    <ul>    -  <b>Creative Content Writing (in English and Indian languages):</b> You will be helping in writing and structuring special articles, giving ideas for various sections and helping in refining the ideas of the other teams.</ul>

    <ul>    -  <b>Language Editing:</b> You would be checking and refining the language of the entire content of the magazine. </ul>

    <ul>    -  <b>Videography and Video Editing:</b> You would be required to help shoot and edit videos for Kalpa's YouTube channel and make reels for its Instagram page.</ul>

    <ul>    -  <b>Designs and Illustrations:</b> You will plan the page layouts and illustrate the articles.</ul>

    <ul>    -  <b>Website Management:</b> This department is in charge of handling Kalpa’s website. They will also be responsible for maintaining and updating it when necessary.</ul>

    <ul>    -  <b>Publicity:</b> This domain entails online and offline publicity for Kalpa. Offline publicity consists of putting up posters on campus, and online publicity involves managing Kalpa’s social media accounts.</ul>


<ul>Drop us a mail here: <a href="mailto: kalpa@sac.iiserpune.ac.in">kalpa@sac.iiserpune.ac.in</a></ul>

</article>

</BaseLayout>
